Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.173, 4. Name Dion. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0344.07.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1196)
